
My face was void of any emotion. However my mind was a disastrous mix of thunders, lighting and murderous hurricanes. It was as wild as nature and as insane as anger.
My eyes were glowing red. I knew it because I could see my vague reflection from the table. My face said nothing but my eyes simply said everything.
The iron door suddenly opened with a harsh squeaky voice as it was the friction of the door and the grey pavement floor.
I was expecting Mr.Arnold but it turned out to be no other than the first General.
General Alex.
